				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm a 65 mage. I have 67 aa's. My guild is not elemental. We have only just killed Saryn. My gear while quite good is not uber. 
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=551821" target="_blank" class="postlink">Wrennegade</a>
<br />

<br />
When I xp, no one out damages me except the odd wizard. I get group invites quickly enough that I count myself fortunate. When I raid, sure my pet dies on PoP boss mobs sometimes but I dont have Pocaliav yet.
<br />

<br />
I hear all this wailing and gnashing of teeth and frankly I don't get it. Go ahead and lay into me for giving the devs the impression that all is well with mages but thats how I see it. Sure I cant solo in tier 2 but I dont think any one should be able to. 
<br />

<br />
I'm excited about the new upcomming AA's and am encouraged to hear that we will be getting an improved pet if it is an improvement in any way.
<br />

<br />
Do we begin to suffer on tier 3 bosses? Tier 4?  Im honestly curious and hope to get some reasonable responses.</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Wrennegade on Sun Feb 08, 2004 10:15 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
			</tr>
