			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">IMHO mage ability and "desireability" oscillates wildly even within a few levels when compared to other classes, be this in a raiding scenario or grouping / soloing. You can be extremely powerful one level and then relegated to the bench two levels later.
<br />

<br />
It also depends on who you are comparing yourself to. L61 mage and L61 wiz with no VT/PoP gear? Mage all the way. L65 mage and L65 wizard both with Time gear? Wizard all the way.
<br />

<br />
It's so hard to consistently compare across a broad range of levels because the answer keeps changing. Beastlords are a little like this as well. Who the hell wants a BL in their 50s? Yet a L65 + max slow + MGB Paragon BL is highly valuable.
<br />

<br />
For example with Nal's post. I totally disagree with respect to levels 60 and 61, compared to other classes mages are powerhouses at this stage of development.
<br />

<br />
From the perspective of a L65 raider a number of classes (that we often perceive ourselves as being in competition with) receive certain upgrades via gear that let them multiply their power and accelerate rapidly away from mages. Many melee get massive weapon upgrades from Tier 3/4 onwards, Wizards get elemental leggings, etc. Mage equipment doesn't provide the same multiplier effect that these bits of gear do.
<br />

<br />
I feel the whole problem with the mage class is the segregation of our power into two streams (melee & spell), it makes us difficult to plan for. Combine that with dodgy mage itemisation and it creates a situation where we have the current lack of "focus of vision" where mages have their own value throughout the whole game spectrum without stepping on other's toes.
<br />

<br />
If you want a quantifiable point at which I started to look at the other classes on a raid and wonder then I'd have to say it starts in the Elementals when elemental pants, massive tank AC/HP from elemental armour, Ifirs, Fiery Staves of Zha and such items start to become common. 
<br />

<br />
Bare in mind this is from my perspective as a raider only. I also always had substantially better gear and AA's than most of my guildies so my perceptions may not be the same as the next mage's. PoP is also unique in that some abilities like charm are totally FUBAR but that's a separate discussion. I just learnt to shake my head and ignore the stupidity that is the enchanter class in PoP and just looked at myself relative to the rest of EQ sans that class.
<br />

<br />
Anyway, I don't think the answer as to "when" we suck is easy. A great many factors influence relative power even in a simple class vs class comparison.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=86257" target="_blank" class="postlink">Zaniel Stormseeker</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of <a href="http://www.afflictionguild.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">Affliction</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
