				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I saw a post by someone recently who claimed to have parses from every LDoN run he's ever done, and who claimed that Pet classes in his groups (whether it's BL or Mage) underperform every time.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Thott and I have talked about this subject.  There are a couple of things at work.
<br />

<br />
1) Thott is a bard and as such his groups always have the benefit of rizlona's. Melee see a much larger benefit from rizlona's than casters and wizards see a much larger benefit than mages.  This accounts for a large part of the discrepency.
<br />
2) His parses do not include pet spells or pet weapon procs.  Once we adjusted for that the numbers were much closer.  Nor did they account for the damage done by a damage shield.
<br />
3) Thott is the puller in his groups which means his dps parses are not complete.  Melee damage is a constant whereas as caster damage is 'spotty'.  In the groups where Thott and I have both parsed I always came out much better in my own parse relative to the other people there.
<br />
4)  I have not seen Thott's post on the subject.  Do you have a link by any chance? But in talking to him, I believe his impression was that wizards consistently underperfom mages so I am curious why that differs from what you read.
<br />
5) The majority of Thott's groups have been LDON normal, which I imagine were finished in under 20 minutes.  This would also skew the picture on wizard damage.
<br />
6) Some of our mages have not maxed out there offensive AA. I have.  One malosinia's a lot in groups, something I find unnescesary.<br />_________________<br />Traigos Ode
<br />
Arch Convoker
