				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">To answer the original poster's question, for raiding viability, Mages become superfluous when Wizards and melee start getting significant gear upgrades. FT, focii, and especially Concussion legs for Wizards, weapons for melee. This tends to be somewhere in the elementals.
<br />

<br />
If your Wizards and Rogues aren't out-damaging the Mages in Time, maybe they need to stop hoarding their DKP or stop cyboring so much. <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="Wink" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Rather than repeat it again, here is some info from Steel Warriors
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?p=117252&highlight=#117252" target="_blank">http://forum.magecompendium.com/viewtopic.php?p=117252&highlight=#117252</a>
<br />

<br />
You suffer about a 25% penalty for swapping in a Mage over a Wizard, about a 5% penalty swapping in a Mage over a Rogue.
<br />

<br />
I have parsed a JTB/DoD Rogue doing consistently over 200 DPS (while in combat, over a three-hour session), ignoring Finishing Blow (the 32k hits are meaningless to a parser).
<br />

<br />
Mages are at best third on the damage list, and I firmly expect them to fall a few notches with the release of GoD. A couple percent boost in pet DPS and in nukes aren't going to keep up with the AAs and gear available to other DPS classes.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=568700" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by itchyban on Mon Feb 09, 2004 6:06 am; edited 3 times in total</span></td>
