<br />
Not pickin' on you Kimberly, this sums up part of my argument well.
<br />

<br />
There is a lot of complaining.  Lots of it.  The funny thing is, <span style="font-weight: bold">every</span> class is complaining.
<br />

<br />
It appears to me that if all the players think they need improvement, then all classes are imbalanced in some way.  Is this possible?  Hmm.
<br />

<br />
The squeeky wheel gets the grease.  Somehow, folks have jumped on this bandwagon assuming they will get attention and their supposed 'issues' addressed.  Problem is, if they're wrong (which most are) they become the ranger that dies in the forest when no one is around.  Does it make a sound?  Nope...not even a peep.
<br />

<br />
I'd liken this to the democrat with no hope of getting chosen for the candidacy for president(US), yet continues out of blind faith, ignorance, or simple spite, to draw votes away from the true contender for their own special interest.  Pathetic.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=195890" target="_blank" class="postlink">Aamen Palantir</a>
