<br />

<br />
I have no doubt that Thott's analysis is very accurate for him, but his analysis was not who is the best all round dps in a group.  His analysis is who is the best all round dps in a group while grouped with a bard with a group that can keep nearly 97% uptime for twenty minute intervals with a twenty minute cool down period afterward.
<br />

<br />
Ultimately who is going to come out on top is going to vary by situation, gear, and group composition.   I have parsed a wide variety of group compositions, and I am fairly comforable with how we perform in relation to other dps classes if all of the following are credited to mages: nukes, pets, pet spells, AA pets, pet procs, and damage shield damage.  the problem is that many of those things aren't  visible and have to be estimated.  Rytan has stated that he has no objection to these things being visible, and I think it something the mage community should really push for.<br />_________________<br />Traigos Ode
