				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Oh -- on DS damage -- might as well throw in that Mages got an LDoN spell that they burn 500 mana on every minute and a half just to keep theri pet alive. Wizards got a targettable spell rune that absorbs 25% of spell damage up to (I believe) 1280 HP. Peridots are basically free for raiding.
<br />

<br />
I would say that a 1280 rune on 70 people is a bit more valuable than a 45-point DS that the MT probably doesn't have a buff slot for.
<br />

<br />
If the pet is doing its usual pathetic 60 DPS against Quarm as it does against other Time mobs (unlikely, as Quarm is usually not cornered), keeping it alive with Callaiv and heals is barely a break-even proposition.
<br />

<br />
And now we get to spend an ungodly amount of AAs to "fix" this? Even after spending the AAs just so pets can survive, we then have to spend AAs on scaling our pets the same way we scaled ourselves. 
<br />

<br />
We are the only DPS class that suffers from both melee- and caster-specific AoEs *and* from melee- and caster-specific AA costs.
<br />

<br />
The problem begins in Tier 2 and grows much worse from there. No, it is not imagination. There are far too many parses and far too many guild-recruitment pages to support that mages do *not* rank well as a DPS class.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=568700" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Itchyban of Veeshan</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
